# UI Components & Windows XP Styling

## Windows XP Design System

### Color Palette
Primary colors used throughout the application:
- **Background**: `#ece9d8` (classic XP beige)
- **Primary Blue**: `#0054e3` (title bars, links)
- **Secondary Blue**: `#316ac5` (hover states)
- **Border Gray**: `#aca899` (panel borders)
- **Text**: `#000000` (primary text)

### Typography
- **Primary Font**: Tahoma, sans-serif (authentic XP font)
- **Fallback**: Arial, sans-serif
- **Sizes**: 11px (default), 12px (headers), 10px (small text)

### 3D Border Effects
Authentic Windows XP borders using CSS:
```css
.xp-panel {
  border: 2px outset #ece9d8;
  background: #ece9d8;
}

.xp-button {
  border: 1px outset #ece9d8;
  background: linear-gradient(to bottom, #ffffff, #ece9d8);
}

.xp-button:active {
  border: 1px inset #ece9d8;
}
```

