## Component Architecture

### Modular CSS Classes
Use BEM methodology with XP prefixes:
```css
.xp-component {}
.xp-component__element {}
.xp-component--modifier {}
```

### JavaScript Component Pattern
```javascript
class XPComponent {
  constructor(container) {
    this.container = container;
    this.init();
  }
  
  init() {
    this.render();
    this.bindEvents();
  }
  
  render() {
    // Component rendering logic
  }
  
  bindEvents() {
    // Event handling
  }
}
```

## Responsive Design

### Breakpoints
- **Desktop**: 1024px+ (primary target)
- **Tablet**: 768px-1023px (adapted XP styling)
- **Mobile**: <768px (simplified XP elements)

### Mobile Adaptations
- Larger touch targets for buttons
- Simplified 3D effects for performance
- Collapsible panels for space efficiency
- Maintained XP color scheme and typography

